node.text:
We are honored legendary quarterback Peyton Manning has signed on as honorary chair of the 2022 Special Olympics Airlift. Last night, Peyton was inducted into the Pro Football Hall of Fame…congratulations!

In this episode of Airlift Answers, Peyton speaks with Connor, a Special Olympics athlete, about Connor’s sporting events, favorite athletes and more.

The Special Olympics Airlift will transport thousands of athletes and coaches to the 2022 @SpecialOlympicsUSAGames next year in Orlando, Fla. To learn more about this monumental aviation event, visit txtav.com/airlift.

#SOA2022 #2022USAGames #FlyCessna #FlyBeechcraft

This week, we welcomed nearly 230 college interns to Textron Aviation!

As a key part of our talent strategy, internships provide both the company and the candidate an opportunity to check each other out to see if they might be a good fit for a future full-time opportunity. The 2021 college interns represent many universities from across the country, including Kansas, Kansas State, Wichita State, Oklahoma, Oklahoma State, Purdue, Embry-Riddle, Iowa State, Arizona State, Texas A&M, Missouri, Miami (Ohio), Clemson and Pittsburg State. The group of interns will support multiple functions throughout the company.

In this video, hear from some previous interns about their experiences!

#TxtAvLife #aviation

Tracy Leopold knew she wanted to work in aviation since she attended airshows with her family as a child. Since joining the company more than 20 years ago, Tracy has served the customer in every aspect and phase of their buying and ownership journey—from aircraft deliveries to Global Parts Sales.

Today, she leads Textron Aviation’s Customer Service Centers in North America. Her strong product expertise, customer focus and drive for continuous improvement positively impacts our customers’ experience and confidence in aftermarket support.

#TxtAvLife

node.text:
We were proud to be the title sponsor of this year’s @CivilAirPatrol National Conference, which was held virtually and wraps up today. Many Civil Air Patrol Cadets begin their aviation journeys in @Cessna aircraft as the CAP has nearly 550 Cessnas in their fleet, including the 172 Skyhawk piston. The Skyhawk has achieved a reputation for being the ultimate training aircraft.

We offer CAP internships at Textron Aviation, which allow college students the opportunity to experience working within the aviation industry and gain more knowledge about our aircraft. The CAP also uses our Cessna 182 Skylane and 206 Turbo Stationair HD aircraft for a variety of missions. Thank you for your continued partnership!

#aviation

In this episode of Airlift Answers, Peyton speaks with Connor, a Special Olympics athlete, about Connor’s sporting events, favorite athletes and more.

The Special Olympics Airlift will transport thousands of athletes and coaches to the 2022 @SpecialOlympicsUSAGames next year in Orlando, Fla. To learn more about this monumental aviation event, visit txtav.com/airlift.
